    <item>
      <title>Re: First 10 days in EQ</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Guides&amp;message.id=184#M184</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;First Ten Days of EQ&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) Be friendly and curtious, and learn to meet people and talk to them with respect.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) Be patient - Leveling takes a great deal of time and patience, plug away at it and do not get discouraged.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) Work on newbie armour quests - this will help teach you how questing in the game works and teach you about the value of keeping certain items around at later levels to do quests&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4) Go through the Tutorial - I know at times the tutorial can be teadious, but it is a great tool to help teach you what features are available and how to use them&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;5) Find and Download Maps that players have made - Will make it much easier for you to get around.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;6) Read the class boards, and do not be afraid to ask questions - Many of the older players who have played EQ for years are more than willing to answer questions if&amp;nbsp;you ask politely.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;7) Learn to respect your fellow players&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;8) Explore -&amp;nbsp;Check out the zones learn the zones, become one with the zones. Learn how to navigate through them&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;9) Experiment - This is allways a big one, but learn how to experiment with your spells and ablitlites, this will help you understand and use each spell / ability to its fullest potential.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;10) Have fun - This is the most important, be social enjoy yourself have fun, lose yourself in the fantasy world.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The biggest thing for an EQ player in his/her infancy is to not panic, with 70 Levels and 1000 or so AA's per class be patient it will take time, take pride in your charcter.&amp;nbsp; In time you will level, if you get stuck or fustrated log off for a while and cool down them come back and try again.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As well one thing I would recommened for all new players, is learning how to travel via the PoK book system and to the bazaar, these will help you find new spells, armour and gear you can purchase.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Last and not least for any new players you need to remember that its a long path to get where you want to go, take it at a speed that will help make the game fun for you.&amp;nbsp; If you like playing 6 to 8 hours daily great, but do not push yourself.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Shardolis Swiftpaw&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;70 Bard Veeshan&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
