    <item>
      <title>Re: First 10 days in EQ</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Guides&amp;message.id=185#M185</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;1) Don't be afraid to ask questions.&amp;nbsp; If you don't ask you don't learn.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) Don't ask other players to give you gear or money.&amp;nbsp; It's considered very bad form.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) Don't be afraid to explore a little bit.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4) Learn the layout of your home city.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;5) Talk to every NPC you can find.&amp;nbsp; Some will give you quests, some may give you game lore, and others may just insult you.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;6) Keep an eye on your food and water supply.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;7) Buy backpacks as soon as you can.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;8) If you have the ability to cast spells, take the time to max out your casting abilities at every level.&amp;nbsp; Find yourself a nice spot and load up one spell for each type (Abjuration, Alteration, Conjuration, Divination, Evocation).&amp;nbsp; Use the lowest level spell of each variety.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;9) Try to visit the bank everytime you sell your loot to a merchant.&amp;nbsp; Coins add up very fast and you can become very encumbered.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
