    <item>
      <title>Re: First 10 days in EQ</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Guides&amp;message.id=183#M183</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;First ten days;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) Learn your home city, explore it, if you die, no biggie after all, your still young.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) Hail every NPC, write down things that sound curious, these may be clues to quests.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) Avoid the EQ forums.&amp;nbsp; The forums are places of ill content, filled with evil trolls that believe that Game play is spelt flameplay.&amp;nbsp; Best to avoid these till after you have enough experience to have your own feel for what you think of the game.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4) Learn the golden rule "exp is not &amp;gt; all"&amp;nbsp; fun is.&amp;nbsp; Have fun, the game is not about leveling, it's about adventuring.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;5) Lastly, explore, have fun, interact.&amp;nbsp; It's a game.&amp;nbsp; If you get to feel it's not.&amp;nbsp; Breath deep, relax, are re-read these 5 rules.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
