    <item>
      <title>Re: First 10 days in EQ</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Guides&amp;message.id=178#M178</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ok, I'm going to list a few things that I wish I had known in my first 10 days of EQ...I hope someone finds them helpful;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;01)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Depending on your race, your vision might not be very good, especially at night.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; a) On your toolbar go to options then display and turn your clip plane and gamma higher.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; b) a fire beetle eye equipped into your secondary slot will help until you can find something better.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;02)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;If your newbie area has "a decaying&amp;nbsp;skeleton" in them, find the ones with long wooden poles in their hand and kill them. Loot the staff,&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; it sells&amp;nbsp;at a good price.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;03)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Find one of each weapon type that you can use, i.e. 1H slash, 1H blunt, 2H slash, 2H Blunt, Piercing, Throwing, Archery, even if it is a rusty version dropped off of "a decaying skeleton".&amp;nbsp; Make sure you fight with each weapon enough to max&amp;nbsp;each skill for your level...&amp;nbsp; it is much easier to raise them as you go than it is to try to catch up.&amp;nbsp; Casters and hybrids should also go into the PoK, where you cannot harm yourself with a spell and cast on your self from each magic type until your skills for each are maxed for your level.&amp;nbsp; Your newbie area will contain a book on a pedestal...this is called a knowledge portal and if you click it, it will teleport you into the plane of knowledge.&amp;nbsp; Nothing except falling damage or a damage over time spell already on you can harm you in here...so do not be afraid in this zone.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;04)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Once you are in the PoK, find the necessities and memorize their locations.&amp;nbsp; Use your find command on your actions bar...the same bar that has the sit and stand buttons on it.&amp;nbsp; Click find and scroll down the list until you find banker dogle pitt....highlight him and click find then follow the golden path...when you see dogle pitt, right click on him...see he is a bank.&amp;nbsp; This is the "small bank" you will hear it referred to from time to time and now you know where it is.&amp;nbsp; Now press find again and select some other banker, follow the golden path until you reach the banker...now you are at the "main bank" or "big bank".&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Once you have enough platinum to make donations, you can donate platinum to other players to cast buffs on you, or if you ask very sweetly might get a few for free....many of the players who sell this as a service do so in this area.&amp;nbsp;Additionally, in front of this bank is the primary location where players will "MGB"&amp;nbsp; MGB means "Mass Group Buff" this is an ability that a higher level player can earn which allows him to cast a buff spell that would normally only effect his group such that it effects everyone for a good distance around him as well.&amp;nbsp; Most of the stuff that is MGB's is for higher level ( 45 and up) players, but at least you now will know what they are all standing there for.&amp;nbsp; Ok, now turn around so that your back is to the banker and walk forward out the door of the bank...continue straight until you reach a arched opening in the wall on your left.&amp;nbsp; Turn left through this opening and walk across the bridge you will come to a intersection in the walkway immediately upon crossing, turn left and stay on the walkway..walk straight until you come to a stone with a low wall around it.. this stone will say "Nexus" remember where this stone is.&amp;nbsp; If you have the Luclin expansion ( if not go buy it..it is a necessity) , click on the stone that says "Nexus" you will be transported into the nexus zone.&amp;nbsp; When you finish zoning if you have a knowledge book right in front of you, turn around so that it is behind you before continuing&amp;nbsp;with this.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Walk forward until you come to an intersecting pathway which leads left and right only.. walk all the way around this pathway...it goes in a circle.&amp;nbsp; As you walk, you will notice several openings on the walled side..these lead to teleport pads and to other zones.&amp;nbsp; In the middle of the circle is a huge teleport pad..this is where you arrive if you are teleported to nexus by a druid, wizard, or necus scion.&amp;nbsp; Continue around the circle again until you come to a passage flanked on one side by a Knight type NPC and on the other side by a female in leather named "Larren"&amp;nbsp; Remember Larren so that you will always no to turn down this path to reach the bazaar.&amp;nbsp; Also, remember that if you face Larren, then turn to your right and walk past the opening and past the Knight type NPC and continue to the next opening flanked by 2 more Knight type NPCs, this is the opening down which the Knowledge Book is located.&amp;nbsp; OK, turn down Larren's pathway and continue straight until you hit a wall.&amp;nbsp; Turn left and continue straight until you come to a wall, turn left again and continue straight until you zone... you are teleported into the Bazaar.&amp;nbsp; Here you can buy and sell things to other players. type /baza and experiment...look what is available.&amp;nbsp; When you are hunting collect spider silks, bone chips, and animal pelts to sell here.&amp;nbsp; You will be able to earn enough to buy armor and weapons here which make the newbie quest armor laughable by comparison, and you will be able to do so in a much shorter time.&amp;nbsp; Learn from my mistake... I wish I had known this.&amp;nbsp; From the bazaar zone in, walk forward to the wall, and turn right...walk along the wall on your right until you come to an opening on your right...this is the zone in to shadowhaven...if you are a caster or hybrid, some spells are sold in there that you cannot find elsewhere, additionally it is an excellent zone for doing tradeskills... at the bottom of shadowhaven, is the zone in to Paludal Caverns near the bandit camp area ( good for lvl 12 - 26 ).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;05) Retrace your steps back to PoK....walk around a find a druid.&amp;nbsp; Ask the druid very nicely if they would mind casting regen and ds on you, if they do not answer, leave them alone, if they say ok, thank them very nicely...remember their name, write it down, return the favor if they ever need anything.&amp;nbsp; DS spell = damage shield, this spell will do damage to anything that strikes you... it will do more damage to a monster than you can.&amp;nbsp; Regen spell = regeneration, this spell will heal damage done to you at a set amount of healing per "tick:"&amp;nbsp; A "tick" is a game term which stands for the amount of time between waves of a spell cast on you.&amp;nbsp; A tick is 6 seconds of real time.&amp;nbsp; So a normal regen, for instance chloroplast would heal 15 hit points of damage per tick ( every 6 seconds ).&amp;nbsp; These 2 spells do not last long so once they are on you make a beeline for your home town stone, or run to the Shar Vahl stone, which is 2 stones away from the "nexus" one.&amp;nbsp; Zone in and start killing monsters...make sure you do at least 1 point of damage to each monster ( everyone in eq calls the monsters "mobs" ) because if you let your damage shield do all the damage, you will not get any experience points.&amp;nbsp; Once you reach level 7-8, follow the path from the shar vahl stone zone in, forward until it ends...turn left and enter the cave like opening there...explore through here until you find the paludal cavern zone in.&amp;nbsp; There is mega experience to be found here.&amp;nbsp; At lvl 15 or so, go to the bandit side we discussed earlier..which is good until lvl 25 or so.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;06)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Do not be afraid to ask for advice, try to pick someone to ask who does not look to be busy at the time.&amp;nbsp; Ask them if they are busy first, if not, ask nicely your question and don't forget to thank them for their advice and time.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Never beg for platinum or items.&amp;nbsp; Additionally, some buff spells cost money to cast because they require a component.&amp;nbsp; Once you learn which spells they are, do not ask for them for free unless you are willing to provide the component to do so.&amp;nbsp; If someone is busy or is bothered when your ask for advice or buffs, apologize for distrubing them and leave them be.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Finally, a tip which I DID do as a youngster, and I highly reccommend to all new players;&amp;nbsp; make a list of all of the things that you had difficulty getting, needed extra help to get, or found very difficult.&amp;nbsp; When you are more experienced and richer, go back to your newbie haunt and help the new players with the things on your list.&amp;nbsp; I go to a newbie zone 2 or 3 times per week to cast a timely heal, buff folks up, and often if I catch someone doing newbie armor quests, to provide them with a invitation to follow me to the bazaar, where I buy them a set of gear and weapons three times as good.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Best of Luck!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
