      <title>Re: First 10 days in EQ</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Guides&amp;message.id=177#M177</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ok, I'm going to list a few things that I wish I had known in my first 10 days of EQ...I hope someone finds them helpful;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;01)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Depending on your race, your vision might not be very good, especially at night.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; a) On your toolbar go to options then display and turn your clip plane and gamma higher.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; b) a fire beetle eye equipped into your secondary slot will help until you can find something better.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;02)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;If your newbie area has "a decaying&amp;nbsp;skeleton" in them, find the ones with long wooden poles in their hand and kill them. Loot the staff,&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; it sells&amp;nbsp;at a good price.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;03)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Find one of each weapon type that you can use, i.e. 1H slash, 1H blunt, 2H slash, 2H Blunt, Piercing, Throwing, Archery, even if it is a rusty version dropped off of "a decaying skeleton".&amp;nbsp; Make sure you fight with each weapon enough to max&amp;nbsp;each skill for your level...&amp;nbsp; it is much easier to raise them as you go than it is to try to catch up.&amp;nbsp; Casters and hybrids should also, go into the PoK, where you cannot harm yourself with a spell and cast on your self from each magic type until your skills for each are maxed for your level.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;04)&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
